        Description copied from interface: AWSServerMigration
        Overrides the default endpoint for this client ("sms.us-east-1.amazonaws.com"). Callers can use this method to control which AWS region they want to work with.

        Callers can pass in just the endpoint (ex: "sms.us-east-1.amazonaws.com") or a full URL, including the protocol (ex: "sms.us-east-1.amazonaws.com"). If the protocol is not specified here, the default protocol from this client's ClientConfiguration will be used, which by default is HTTPS.

        For more information on using AWS regions with the AWS SDK for Java, and a complete list of all available endpoints for all AWS services, see: http://developer.amazonwebservices.com/connect/entry.jspa?externalID=3912

        This method is not threadsafe. An endpoint should be configured when the client is created and before any service requests are made. Changing it afterwards creates inevitable race conditions for any service requests in transit or retrying.
